F

Field - Class in edu.fresno.uniobjects.data
A Field is a wrapper for three pieces of information about a UniData field: The name of the field (eg FIRST.NAME) The friendly name of the field (eg fname) The data the field contains, if created by UniDataConnection.getFields(FieldDefinition)
Field() - Constructor for class edu.fresno.uniobjects.data.Field
Create a field with no data
Field(String, String) - Constructor for class edu.fresno.uniobjects.data.Field
Create a Field, specifying the field name and the user-friendly field name.
FieldDefinition - Class in edu.fresno.uniobjects.data
FieldDefinition is an object that represents a set of data that should be retrieved from the UniData data source.
FieldDefinition(String) - Constructor for class edu.fresno.uniobjects.data.FieldDefinition
Construct a new FieldDefinition, specifying only the file.
FieldDefinition(String, List<Field>) - Constructor for class edu.fresno.uniobjects.data.FieldDefinition
Construct a new FieldDefinition, specifying the file and the fields.

FieldSet - Class in edu.fresno.uniobjects.data
A FieldSet is a wrapper for a List of Fields, used when returning data from UniDataConnection.getFields(FieldDefinition).
